items.title: Betts' second 20-20 season a Red Sox first
items.summary: The combination of power and speed that Mookie Betts possesses hasn't been seen often in Red Sox history, and that was made evident with the right fielder's moonshot over the Green Monster in the bottom of the fourth inning on Monday night.

items.title: Dozier notches 2nd straight 30-HR season
items.summary: With his leadoff homer against the Padres on Wednesday, Brian Dozier became the fifth Twins player to hit 30 homers in consecutive seasons and the first Major League second baseman to do it since Dan Uggla from 2007-11.
